sentence.text: Variants of WNK1 (lysine deficient protein kinase 1), ADRB2 (b2 adrenergic receptor), NEDD4L (ubiquitin-protein ligase ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process-like), KLK1 (kallikrein 1) contribute to hypertension, and AKR1C3 (aldo-keto reductase family1 member C3), is associated with preeclampsia.
